<hl>
<seg id=1> Economic cooperation conference of Henan Province and foreign-funded financial institutions held in Beijing </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Beijing, December 26 (Xinhua News Agency) The government of Henan Province is holding a talk here with over 100 representatives from 88 foreign funded financial institutions in Beijing, with the purpose of promoting understanding between Henan Province and the international financial world and to find new fund circulation channels for the economic development of Henan Province. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> Chen Yuan, President of the People's Bank of China said in a greeting letter to the meeting that, the Chinese government has decided to strengthen the development and opening up of the mid-western areas, encourage enterprises home and abroad to invest in these areas, and from now on, make 60% of the foreign bank loans and government loans serve the middle west area. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> Kexiye, Chairman of the foreign funded financial institutions in Beijing, Chief Representative of the Belgium General Bank's deputy office to Beijing, said that, all the foreign financial institutions in Beijing intend to make efforts for economic development of Henan Province and for the opening up of China's mid-western areas. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> The Executive Deputy Governor of Henan Province Li Chengyu briefed on Henan's natural resources and economic development. </seg>
<seg id=6> He said, Henan not only has the infrastructure needed for foreign investment, but also makes preferential policies for foreign investors and the development of cooperation on foreign trade and technology, according to the state policies and the real situation of our province. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> Relevant sections of the Henan Government released their foreign cooperation projects concerning economy and technology. Representatives attending the meeting consulted on information of some projects they interested in. </seg>
</p>
